<TITLE> CMC suspends 4 BCL men on rape charges </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Feb 23 (bdnews24.com)  Chittagong Medical College has suspended four students, known to be Bangladesh Chhatra League leaders and activists, on allegations of raping a girl. The college's principal Selim Md Jahangir told bdnews24.com that the decision was taken at an emergency academic council meeting on Tuesday noon. The four have been named as Chhatra League's CMC unit assistant general secretaries Kazi Faisal and Afibul Islam Limon and BCL activists Shohag and Rabbi. Allegations were made against them of raping a girl on a hill adjoining the campus on Thursday night. The college took steps after the allegations spread through the campus. The identity of the girl was not made public and no rape case has been filed at the local police station. b
